'''''Fire in the Night''''' is a 2013 British [[documentary film]] about the [[Piper Alpha]] disaster directed by [[Anthony Wonke]].<ref name="BBC">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-23100125 |title=Edinburgh Film Festival rewards Piper Alpha documentary |accessdate=30 June 2013 |work=BBC News |date=28 June 2013}}</ref> It won the Audience Award at the 2013 [[Edinburgh International Film Festival]].<ref name="Scotsman">{{Cite web|url=http://www.scotsman.com/edinburgh-evening-news/latest-news/festival-film-award-goes-to-trawler-movie-1-2983565 |title=Festival film award goes to trawler movie |accessdate=30 June 2013 |work=Scotsman}}</ref><ref name="Guardian">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2013/jun/28/edinburgh-film-festival-awards-leviathan |title=Edinburgh gives top award to experimental documentary Leviathan |accessdate=30 June 2013 |work=The Guardian |location=London |first=Andrew |last=Pulver |date=28 June 2013}}</ref> It was first shown on television on 9 July 2013 on [[BBC Two]], three days after the 25th anniversary of the disaster.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/proginfo/2013/28/fire-in-the-night.html|title= Piper Alpha: Fire In The Night|work= BBC Media Centre|accessdate= 9 July 2013}}</ref>

