The '''Mt Stuart Wind Farm''' is a [[wind farm]] in New Zealand constructed by Pioneer Generation. It is located 15 kilometres west of [[Milton, New Zealand|Milton]] in the [[Otago]] region of the South Island.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.pioneergen.co.nz/Projects.aspx| title=Current Projects: Mt Stuart Wind| publisher=Pioneer| accessdate=8 November 2011}}</ref>
Resource consents were granted in February 2010.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.odt.co.nz/your-town/milton/107013/wind-farm-firm-sourcing-turbines| title=Wind farm firm sourcing turbines| first=Hamish| last=McNeilly| date=21 May 2010| publisher=Otago Daily Times}}</ref> Construction began in April 2011<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.odt.co.nz/regions/south-otago/171810/preparing-power-tower| title=Preparing for power tower| first=Helena| last=de Reus| publisher=Otago Daily Times| date=3 August 2011}}</ref> and the nine turbine wind farm was commissioned in December 2012.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.odt.co.nz/regions/south-otago/213484/otago-wind-power-eating-your-own-veges| title=Otago wind power 'like eating your own veges'| first=Helena| last=de Reus| publisher=Otago Daily Times| date=16 June 2012}}</ref>
