The '''Mutriku Breakwater Wave Plant''' is a [[wave power plant]] commissed by
the Basque Energy Agency in the bay of [[Mutriku]] in the [[Bay of Biscay]] and is the world's first breakwater wave power plant with a multiple turbine arrangement.<ref>[http://www.voithhydro.com/media/HyPower16_S.53.pdf First breakwater wave plant built in Mutriku]</ref> The plant has a capacity of 300&nbsp;kW from 16 [[turbo generator]] sets.<ref>[http://www.eve.eus/EVE/media/EVE/pdf/Mutriku-2016.pdf Mutriku power plant]</ref> It was inaugurated on July 8, 2011.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20110710021755/http://www.noticiasdegipuzkoa.com/2011/07/07/sociedad/euskadi/mutriku-cuenta-con-la-primera-planta-europea-que-suministra-energia-de-las-olas Mutriku cuenta con la primera planta europea ...] ''(in Spanish)''</ref><ref>[http://www.bild.de/regional/stuttgart/stuttgart-regional/erstes-kommerzielles-wellenkraftwerk-geht-18748292.bild.html Erstes kommerzielles Wellenkraftwerk geht in Betrieb] ''(in German)''</ref>

