{{Infobox Union |name= SEF |country= [[Sweden]] |affiliation= [[Swedish Trade Union Confederation|LO]] |members= 24,775 (2011)<ref>{{cite journal |author=Wreder, Johanna | title=Men medlemstappet går långsammare |journal=LO-tidningen. | volume=2011 | issue=26 |pages=7}}</ref> |full_name= Swedish Electricians' Union |native_name= Svenska Elektrikerförbundet |image= [[Image:SEF logo.png|125px]] |founded= 1906 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Stockholm]], Sweden |people= Jonas Wallin, president |website= [http://www.sef.com www.sef.com] |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''Swedish Electricians' Union''' (''Svenska Elektrikerförbundet'': SEF) is a [[trade union]] in [[Sweden]]. It has a membership of 24,775 (in 2011) and represents electricians in light and heavy instillations, as well as radio, TV and electronics technicians and power station staff.
SEF is affiliated with the [[Swedish Trade Union Confederation]].
