'''''What Is the Electric Car?''''' is a 2010 [[documentary film]] that explains the benefits of electric cars.  One reviewer stated that the movie "teeters on the brink of tedious but repeatedly saves itself with moments of cleverness or insight."<ref>{{cite web|last=Trabish|first=Herman|title=Film Review: Who Killed Electric Car II Interesting, But…|url=http://www.greentechmedia.com/articles/read/what-the-electric-car-is/|publisher=Greentech Media|accessdate=January 5, 2011}}</ref>  The film features several actors, scientists, engineers and activists, all of whom contribute their thoughts and explanations regarding electric cars and electric vehicle technology.

The film premiered on December 14, 2010 at the [[Grauman's Egyptian Theatre|Egyptian Theatre]] in [[Hollywood|Hollywood, California]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Blanco|first=Sebastion|title=Hollywood premiere for "What Is the Electric Car?" happening tonight|url=http://green.autoblog.com/2010/12/14/hollywood-premiere-for-what-is-the-electric-car-happening-ton/|publisher=autobloggreen|accessdate=January 6, 2011}}</ref>

